passages.text: ASIA- PACIFIC excl. Japan | Autos & Auto Parts Great Wall Motor- A
Equity Research August 31, 2025

GWM reported in- line 2Q results with its prelim announcement, with rev up \(31\%\) YoY to RMB52.3bn and NP reaching RMB4.6bn vs. RMB1.8bn in 1Q25. Core earnings stood at RMB2.1bn, up from RMB1.5bn in 1Q25. GPM declined 2.6ppt YoY but rose 1ppt QoQ. GWM expects 2H25 sales to grow by \(40\% - 50\%\) HoH and aims to reclaim its top 3 position among Chinese OEMs over the next 3- 5 years. GWM's comeback story, in our view, has just begun. Reiterate Buy as our conviction pick.

2Q in line with earnings quality better than expected. 1) In 2Q25, GWM's SG&A/R&D expenses to sales ratios were \(7\% /4.5\%\) down 1ppt and 0.3ppt QoQ, respectively, reflecting an improvement in operational efficiency despite the ongoing investment in WEY/Tank's direct store expansion. 2) mgmt. acknowledged that GPM of Russia sales declined 3- 4ppt on fluctuations in scrappage tax. However, overall, the Russian market remains profitable, thanks to its local facility. 3) export profitability levels of Tank and pickups are comparable to domestic sales, while Haval's profitability exceeds domestic GPM by \(>5\) ppt.

Sales volume in 2H25 is expected to grow by \(40\% - 50\%\) HoH. Mgmt. mentioned that Order momentum for both new Big Dog and Tank 500 Hi4Z has exceeded expectations. GWM expects Tank 400 and 700 to potentially double in sales upon launch of their "city home" versions. In Sep, WEY's Gaoshan7 will start mass deliveries, followed by the mid- to- large luxury SUV built on WEY's new platform in 4Q25 or early 2026. Ora's new platform models will debut with 1- 2 launches in 4Q25. Ora EC15 will be positioned for mass market with an attractive price point.

Aiming to exceed 1mn units in export sales by 2030, with localized production progressing smoothly. The Brazil plant, now operational, is strategically positioned to serve the broader Latin American market and functions as a key hub linking Europe, Southeast Asia, and Latin America. Mgmt indicated that localized production in Brazil offers a cost advantage of thousands RMB per car over direct CBU imports. In 1H, export markets outside of Russia recorded YoY rise of \(30\% - 190\%\) . With this momentum, GWM is confident to achieve 500k units in export sales in 2025.

Returning to glory, GWM has often been overlooked by investors due to its slower electrification progress relative to peers - a dynamic we believe stems from its strategic emphasis on profitability, rather than any deficiency in EV technologies. With the launch of new EV platforms under ORA and WEY, we believe GWM is set to reclaim its leadership position in fact, the company has built a wide moat by creating niche and lucrative categories including off- roaders and hybrid HDTs, and its early investments in high- potential markets like Russia and Latin America are now poised to deliver meaningful returns. We adjust our 2025/26 earnings forecasts to RMB15.9/18.8bn. Our PTs are raised to RMB37.0 for GWM- A and HK \(26.8 for GWM - H\) as we roll forward the valuation base to 2026 with product schedule being more clear. Reiterate Buy.

There is a visible strong cycle of new models, such as ORA's cat series, Tank's SUVs, Wey's coffee series, which will sustain GWM's growth. GWM is the clear leader in niche markets like pickup and offroad vehicles, so competitors will find it difficult to duplicate its success. GWM's adoption of a full- stack self- developed AD system will enhance its long- term competitiveness.
Risk/Reward - 12 Month View
Margins improve with rising sales of premium products under Tank Brand and Wey Brand. Export sales reach 500k units in 2025. A/HP T of RMB37/HKD26.8 based on 18x/12x 2026E EPS.

Macro recovery leads to stronger auto sales. High- than- expected sales of smart EVs under the WEY brand. High- than- expected sales of offroad vehicles under Tank. Favorable policies boost the pickup market. A/HP T Rmb51.4/HK\$33.5 based on 25x/15x 2026E EPS.

Macro deterioration leads to weaker auto sales. More severe competition in SUV and pickup segments. Failures in AD system development. Failure of the upscaling strategy with L3 model launches. A/HP T of Rmb20.6/HK\$13.4 based on 10x/6x 2026E EPS.
Top Material Issue(s):

1. Product quality and safety are identified as the most important corporate issues by GWM. GWM needs to improve the product quality management system to ensure that products meet applicable regulations and are eco-friendly, safe, and reliable. 
2. GWM must improve the safety and health system and strengthen the management of the safety information platform so that the process of production will be in line with stakeholders' requirements.
Stronger-than- expected margins Better- than- expected sales of new models Successful launches of smart EVs Successful development of AD systems BMW JV begins operations in 2024.

1. Plan to achieve carbon neutrality by 2045. Aim to build its first zero-carbon factory by 2023 through the adjustment of energy structure and the application of low-carbon technology. 
3. Launch more than 50 new energy vehicles in 2025.

1. How do you ensure safe production? What is the monitoring process and who is responsible for safe production? 
2. What are you investing in to reach carbon neutrality?

Great Wall Motor Company Limited, through its subsidiaries, manufactures and sells pick- up trucks and sport- utility vehicles (SUVs) in China under branded names. The company also researches and develops, and manufactures principal automotive parts and components for use in the assembly of pick- up trucks and SUVs.

Buy - Describes securities that we expect to provide a total return (price appreciation plus yield) of \(15\%\) or more within a 12- month period. Hold - Describes securities that we expect to provide a total return (price appreciation plus yield) of plus \(15\%\) or minus \(10\%\) within a 12- month period. Underperform - Describes securities that we expect to provide a total return (price appreciation plus yield) of minus \(10\%\) or less within a 12- month period.

The expected total return (price appreciation plus yield) for Buy rated securities with an average security price consistently below \(10 is 20\%\) or more within a 12- month period as these companies are typically more volatile than the overall stock market. For Hold rated securities with an average security price consistently below \(10, the expected total return (price appreciation plus yield) is plus or minus 20% within a 12- month period. For Underperform rated securities with an average security price consistently below\) 10, the expected total return (price appreciation plus yield) is minus 20% or less within a 12- month period.

Jefferies Franchise Picks will include only Buy rated stocks and the number can vary depending on analyst recommendations for inclusion. Stocks will be added as new opportunities arise and removed when the reason for inclusion changes, the stock has met its desired return, if it is no longer rated Buy and/or if it triggers a stop loss. Stocks having 120 day volatility in the bottom quartile of S&P stocks will continue to have a 15% stop loss, and the remainder will have a 20% stop. Franchise Picks are not intended to represent a recommended portfolio of stocks and is not sector based, but we may note where we believe a Pick falls within an investment style such as growth or value.
